WUTHERING HEIGHTS. 2 1

CHAPTER II.

ABOUT twelve o’clock, that night, was born
the Catherine you saw at \Vutbering Heights,
:1 puny, seven months’ child; and two hours
after the mother died, having never recovered
sufﬁcient consciousness to miss Heathcliff, or
know Edgar.

The 1atter’s distraction at his bereavement
is a subject too painful to be dwelt on; its
after effects showed how deep the sorrow sunk.

A great addition, in my eyes, was his being

left without an heir. I bemoancd that, as I

